title: For Sale:  VZ2008 rifle - new, unfired + mags, bayonet, cleaning kit, pouch
postcontent:
For sale is a VZ2008 rifle in 7.62x39 with a folding stock. Although this looks like an AK47, it is different in several respects. First, it has a solid milled receiver -- unlike the stamped sheet metal you find on AK-pattern rifles. Second, it uses a striker fired action that its Czech designers felt was superior to the Soviet AK. The rifle has never been fired, so it's truly in new condition. It is flawless. It comes with five 30-round magazines, four of which are still sealed in the factory plastic. It sports the original Czech resin furniture, as does the bayonet that is also included. The bayonet has its original surplus leather scabbard. The scabbard has been decorated by what I'm guessing were soldiers during the Balkans conflicts during the 1990s. There are several pen drawings on it with 1990s references and Cyrillic characters. Pretty cool. In addition to all of the above, I'm including a brand-new Czech military surplus shoulder bag to hold the magazines or whatever else you'd like.

*** Also includes original surplus cleaning kit!

This is a great option to shoot two great calibers, and do it without spending money on two uppers, and two optics. The barrel can be changed in less than 2 minutes. LMT is one of the best in the business, on par or better than any AR manufacturer. Upper was cerakoted FDE.

- MRP upper new without the brake is $1250-$1400 (never fired)
- 8.5" .300 blk barrel assembly Noveske barrel w/ AAC 51T Brakeout 2.0 ($800)
- Nickel Boron Fail Zero DI bolt and BCG ($250)
- 10.5" LMT Barrel 5.56 w/ Brake
- AAC muzzle devices are $100x3 
- 12.5" complete piston barrel and assembly w/ POF roller cam upgrades (fired for function) w/ piston LMT BCG are $750-$950 w/ upgrades
- Gas buster charging handle (for suppressed fire) new, $115

The 10.5" 5.56 is DI LMT barrel w/ a AAC 51T Brake. never fired

The 8.5 .300 BLK is a Noveske barrel custom made for use w/ a MRP platform.

The 12.5" piston barrel assembly was upgraded with a POF rollercam upgrade which has significantly smoothed carrier travel. And the plug on the piston is not the standard plug it is the upgraded version, that is offered by LMT's, that is for suppressed and unsuppressed fire. The difference between the standard plug and the upgraded plug is the standard plug only has one side that is open for fire the other is closed. Where as with the suppressed and non-suppressed plug there are holes on both sides of the plug to better regulate gas flow for when you are running either non-suppressed or suppressed fire. (The piston configuration was used with my other MRP, ~120 rounds to function test it.)

Package as is value is easily $3k, I know I'm not going to get $3k so asking $2.5k cash (OBO), open to trades. Going to put this on GB, but thought I'd list locally first.

Feel free to respond w/ questions or trades, or text me at REDACTED

I am really looking to get into a SCAR, but shoot me a reasonable offer and I will consider, thanks!

title: For Sale/Trade:  4,310 Rounds of AK-47 Ammo
postcontent:
For sale / trade are 4,310-rounds of factory 7.62 x 39mm ammo.  

I no longer have my AK-47 and I believe the days of having an in-depth plan for bugging out are behind us.  So I am selling a massive amount of 7.62 x 39mm ammo.  

Here is a breakdown of the 4,310-rounds:

122 grain FMJ (x 2,480)
123 grain FMJ (x 510)  
123 grain HP (x 140) 
124 grain FMJ (x 200)
154 grain SP (x 80)
Assorted factory ammo in full boxes (x 900) 

Pricing – I looked up the cheapest price I could find online (Sportsmansguide.com) and the largest lots they sold the ammo in (for lowest price) and I went below that price.  Yes, I am charging less – and they don’t even have the large quantities in stock, plus no tax, no shipping, and no membership fee.  

This is more than a weekends worth of fun!  You could store 4,000 rounds and still have enough for a fun range trip.  Plus the variety of ammo allows you to select your round based on use instead of just what happens to be in stock at Walmart.  

There are some battle packs included with the count above.  There are also three ammo cans and one ammo crate included.  

All of the ammo is labeled as non-corrosive.  Despite that, most of it is made in former Soviet-bloc countries and you should always assume it is corrosive; I believe that’s true of all ammo from those parts of the world.
